To give a quick paraphrase of what Carro and Const are talking about in the Spaces above: Bittensor's ability to consume literally any technology enables people to build any product on top. We have an experimental release on the prompting network which will make it easier for everyone to talk to the prompting network.
She is still reaching equilibrium but we are finally getting some consistent results. Very exciting.

```bash
pip install bittensor==4.1.0rc1.post2
```

And prompting is as easy as this:
```python
import bittensor as bt; bt.prompt('What is the capital of Tattoine?)
```

You can also connect into Langchain and replace the OpenAI llm with Bittensor to make your app unstoppable
```python
import bittensor as bt
llm = bt.BittensorLLM()
llm('What is the capital of Texas?')
```

The more of us that query into the network, the quicker it accumulates knowledge and the faster we can build the best ML system in the world. Every prompt we give into the network is data we are accumulating which is going into a dataset we can use to train more miners on the network.

Bittensor is not a Polkadot Parachain--it is a standalone Substrate chain. Substrate is the tech behind polkadot (built by Parity, the team that built Polkadot), so Substrate accounts can be managed with Polkadot ecosystem wallets like Polkadot.js, Talisman, and Nova.
In the past, there was a plan for Bittensor to become a Parachain, and a Parachain slot was acquired (self-funded, no Crowdloan), but the team decided against it, for now at least.

There is no risk.  When you delegate to a validator, the validator is using your Tao to earn additional rewards and increase its position on the network.  The validator does not have access to your staked Tao and cannot take them, even if operating maliciously: your Tao is never forfeited nor are the additional gains you receive in the form of Tao at a rate of 100% - x% of that validator’s rate (where "x" is the "take", or commission, that the validator owner has specified; the default is 18%). 

If the validator goes down, both you and the validator stop earning Tao. At that point, you can unstake your Tao (including any gains you earned while validator was running) and the validator keeps their portion of the additional gains from your your Tao (whatever "take" the validator operator has specified.).  Your original stake and rewards earned are never in jeopardy and can be unstaked at any time, though there is a limit to one (1) stake OR unstake operation every 360 blocks (approximately 1.2 hours), so if you try to unstake and then immediately restake, it won't work (and that's normal - just wait and try again later).

For figuring out which validator(s) you want to support, you can find most of their operators in the TAO Community Discord (here: https://discord.gg/phuyC2aEVK), which is also the place to go if you've liked to ask questions about specific validators, if you're looking for validators that share your goals & ideals, or otherwise looking for validators that will meet your requirements.

And here is the official, verified list of validators: https://github.com/opentensor/bittensor-delegates/blob/main/public/delegates.json

We won't be able to make recommendations to you, but you can check them out yourself (and a good source for raw metrics is at Taostats: https://taostats.io). : )

Es besteht kein Risiko. Wenn Sie an einen Validator delegieren, verwendet der Validator Ihr Tao, um zusätzliche Belohnungen zu erhalten und seine Position im Netzwerk zu verbessern. Der Validator hat keinen Zugriff auf Ihr eingesetztes Tao und kann es nicht nehmen, selbst wenn er in böswilliger Absicht handelt: Ihr Tao verfällt nie, ebenso wenig wie die zusätzlichen Gewinne, die Sie in Form von Tao zu einem Satz von 100% - x % des Satzes dieses Validators’erhalten (wobei "x" der „Einsatz“ oder die Provision ist, die der Validatorbesitzer angegeben hat; der Standardwert ist 18%). 

Wenn der Validator ausfällt, verdienen sowohl Sie als auch der Validator kein Tao mehr. An diesem Punkt können Sie Ihr Tao zurücknehmen (einschließlich aller Gewinne, die Sie erzielt haben, während der Validator lief) und der Validator behält seinen Anteil an den zusätzlichen Gewinnen aus Ihrem Tao (welchen „Einsatz“ auch immer der Validatorbetreiber angegeben hat.). Ihr ursprünglicher Einsatz und die verdienten Belohnungen sind nie in Gefahr und können jederzeit zurückgenommen werden, obwohl es ein Limit von einem (1) Einsatz ODER Rücknahmevorgang alle 360 Blöcke (ungefähr 1.2 Stunden) gibt, also wird es nicht funktionieren, wenn Sie versuchen, den Einsatz zurückzunehmen und dann sofort wieder einzusetzen (und das ist normal – warten Sie einfach und versuchen Sie es später erneut).

Um herauszufinden, welchen/welche Validierer Sie unterstützen möchten, finden Sie die meisten ihrer Betreiber in der TAO-Community Discord (hier: https://discord.gg/phuyC2aEVK).
